Vet Centers to launch in Marianas

"These outreach visits by the Guam Vet Center are an important first step in the right direction. Our ultimate goal is to establish a Vet Center of our own, right here in the Northern Marianas." - @Kilili_Sablan

As Ranking Member of the @HELPCmteDems I opened our joint hearing w/ the Workforce Protection Subcommittee on the #opioid epidemic last Thursday. We need stronger consumer protections & greater access to treatment thru Medicaid & others to combat this problem. https://t.co/tz8YRPuSRw

#VeteransAffairs Secretary @SecShulkin invited Committee members to breakfast at the Department‚Äôs headquarters Wednesday. We discussed the President‚Äôs FY19 funding request for the VA in preparation for our oversight hearing on the budget the next day. https://t.co/fz3fYbU2l4

Students at Tinian Elem. &  Jr./Sr. High School, as well as patrons of the Tinian Public Library received 60 boxes of books hand-selected by your congressional office from @librarycongress. Via the Surplus Books program, nearly 45,000 books have been brought to the NMI. https://t.co/8lErMXCnl2

Tinian Mayor Joey San Nicolas reviewed the positive impacts my U.S. Workforce Act will have for Tinian. We also talked strategies for further funding the Tinian Harbor project. The Army Corps of Engineers is currently conducting a feasibility study that I was able to authorize. https://t.co/pmiYrlGQRm

Over the last few days, I've been writing pieces in the @Saipan__Tribune, breaking down the NMI US Workforce Act. This is the first in a 4-part series. Each new piece will be added as a new tweet in this thread.

At the Senate hearing for the NMI US Workforce Act, I detailed how the bill would protect foreign workers from unfair labor practices. We must protect the livelihoods of all workers who choose to work in the Marianas. @GoldMantisLabor https://t.co/q7RM7jfh6r

The 1st hearing for the U.S. Workforce Act, which I intro'd in the House and @lisamurkowski in the Senate, is set for tomorrow (Wed. 1am in the NMI, Tue. 10am in DC). I will be outlining the bill to the Senate Energy and Natural Resources Committee, which @lisamurkowski chairs.

Last Thursday, the Society for Human Resource Management, who are at the front line of labor issues here, asked me to go over details of the new Sablan/Murkowski U.S. Workforce Act. The bill addresses many of the problems human resources professionals face in their businesses. https://t.co/LTZIwRgOe6

Last week @ a panel discussion on labor&workforce issues, I asked experts advice on building an apprenticeship program in the NMI. Gov. Torres, his staff and members of the NMI business community met with me at my Washington office Monday. We all agreed that the Trump administration decision to cut the number of CW permits this year to 9,998 was not what we wanted. For more: https://t.co/SWpH34l4NE https://t.co/R1HjrEtfPt

To those who've already followed this account: 

We now are at the handle @Kilili_Sablan and no longer @SablanKilili. We are now working on Twitter verification. Thank you for your patience as we set up this account.
